subtitle: for many people
virtually everything in their lives is
spurious
we are raised by well-meant adults that
paint our minds with an archaic and
obsolete mentality
our lives are strictly guided towards
paths chosen by these adult figures in
our lives
and we follow without questions because
we trust their judgment
often born out of long years of
experience
we will eventually get to a point in our
lives where all these lessons learned
over the years become practicalized
and then we go into the nine-to-five
world where we work to pay the bills
and only live for the weekends our lives
are plunged into an almost
unending cycle of subservience to an
employer for the most part
of our youth living someone else's
dreams
we have become so detached from
ourselves that we ignore the warning
signals being sent by our system
we try to convince ourselves that we
have achieved enough at work
and attempt to get a shot at the
comfortable life in the evening
following the standard specially
prepared by the media
we allow ourselves to be distracted by
this superficial entertainment and
conveniently ignore the real struggle
faced by many people
in the outside world we allow ourselves
to be run
following the dictates of flamboyant ads
we get immersed in their realm of
infinite consumerism scenarios
stacking our refrigerators with food we
can't cook
and with food that we waste later we're
wasting huge amounts of food that the
less privileged people around the globe
would be thankful for
we've been blindly led into these
wasteful norms that
we become afraid and embarrassed to go
against these norms
we don't see the need to reduce our
wasteful habits and recycle our garbage
or the need to prevent pollution simply
because others are not doing it
you can detach yourself from this herd
behavior and advocate for new and
healthier trends
most people are wallowing in ignorance
paying no mind to the world around them
most people have become so closed-minded
that they fail to see what's going on
around the globe so self-entitled to the
point of taking their lives for granted
it is important to take a step back and
re-evaluate our lives
while we are worrying over more likes on
social media
children in other parts of the world are
worrying over food and water
while you are sick and tired of the
weather people in australia are
suffering from the heat of calamitous
brush fires
while you make incessant complaints
about your life people in other parts of
the world would give anything to have
even a slice of what you have
we have been nurtured with fear from the
formative years of our lives and this
fear has metamorphosed into adulthood
we are frightened by the thought that
maybe the truth we have been served
is nothing but a hoax so we continue to
live in our web of lies
in fear of not conforming with the norms
by accusing others
we bow to the elites that use us to
achieve their goals
we refuse to allow ourselves to think of
the possibilities of a world outside the
small box we have crammed into
every move we make is by the dictates of
these greedy elites
they are controlling us their aim is to
gain a strong control
of the masses take a critical look at
politics and how these political
games affect our lives and how we accept
them consciously by voting
these politicians instill fear in us as
a campaign strategy
and we follow blindly as they make up
stories of enemies that are non-existent
we judge everything that's not aligned
with our view failing to see that
diversity could be a good thing
we act like our persistent existence
will last forever
and that's why we postpone calls to
loved ones like they'd be there at all
times
life is limited and it lasts more or
less for every one of us
life is not promised stop postponing
we make complaints about back and neck
pains but our eyes are fixated on our
devices at all time
that we totally ignore the effects on
our body in a bid to be social online
we have forgotten how to hold real
conversations with people offline
we fill our heads with the wrong
versions of what happiness should look
like
we are consistently seeking validation
via social media likes and comments
why can't we be smart about our smart
devices
why aren't we using this amazing tool to
spread knowledge and healing to the
world
we've inadvertently allowed technology
to use us
instead of the other way around a lot is
happening around us
even in our immediate environments that
we have completely ignored
nature has changed over the years and
were the main culprits
we place a lot of attention on
technological advancements and erecting
buildings at the detriment of nature
we take virtually everything from nature
without giving back
look at the mess we made with force in
our quest to build a sophisticated
society
we're killing vegetation and in turn
killing our source of carbon dioxide
removal from the air and
supporting greenhouse gas emissions it's
been established that deforestation is
the second leading cause of climate
change
we have polluted our seas lakes and
oceans
we're greatly surprised when we see
people struggling with smelly and dirty
water in the media
did you know that there are people who
resort to using contaminated water daily
a study conducted by the environmental
working group in 2018
revealed that about 14 million americans
are using contaminated water with a
cancer-causing industrial solvent
things didn't change even after this
grim revelation
why are we so self-centered that nothing
around us matters anymore
why are we teaching our children to
satisfy their needs
and completely ignore the repercussions
of their actions on the environment
we need to come back to our senses
before things get exacerbated
what we have done thus far is irrelevant
what matters is changing our ways of
doing things
and restoring the balance one step at a
time
the media and politics will not bring
forth the desired change
we are the change gradually we can
create new trends and enlighten those
ignorant of the planet's flight
we can start little because little steps
taken in the process of caring more
about the effects of our actions
can bring about huge and significant
reformation
we need to hold ourselves accountable
for all the things we do with our lives
we can't sit idly by and wait for others
to make a change when we can make a
change
the time to act is now at this very
moment we could be in
any corner of the world and be thinking
about ourselves
we could be watching tv on our cozy
couch while looking at our smartphones
to see how many likes our posts garnered
or complaining about this sluggish
internet connection
or the unavailability of our favorite
soap opera on netflix
we could be bothering ourselves with
anything that adds no direct value to
our lives
but what are we doing to add value to
the lives of others
we keep taking and taking from nature
but what exactly are we giving back
we take amazing photos of the greenery
and awe-inspiring aesthetics of nature
in our trips
and share on social media but are we
doing something to keep it green
and beautiful for others to savor we
talk about the good deeds that we're
doing for kids in need of help on
holidays but
what are we doing for them in other
months of the year
their lives will not change simply
because we gave them that one gift
during the holidays
the best legacy we can leave behind for
our kids is a clean
green and beautiful world the
technologies we enjoy today are due to
the efforts of our forebears
to make life better for us this includes
vehicles
electricity telephones and a host of
other beneficial technological
innovations that we are taking for
granted these days
we can play a role in making life better
for the next age
we can create something they can all be
proud of and be thankful for in the
future
why not etch your footprints in the
sands of time as the generation that
made the world a better place
